        <h2><span class="emoji">üìå</span> 3. Algorithm Selection & Implementation (Required) Documented Algorithm Selection Rationale</h2>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Algorithm Name</th>
                    <th>Type</th>
                    <th>Rationale for Selection</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Caesar Cipher</td>
                    <td>Simple</td>
                    <td>Entry-level algorithm to demonstrate basic principles of substitution ciphers; educational value</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Atbash Cipher</td>
                    <td>Simple</td>
                    <td>Entry-level algorithm to demonstrate basic principles of substitution ciphers; educational value</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Vigen√®re Cipher</td>
                    <td>Intermediate</td>
                    <td>Shows evolution beyond simple ciphers with multiple shift values; historically significant</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>XOR Cipher</td>
                    <td>Intermediate</td>
                    <td>Demonstrates binary operations in cryptography; foundation for many stream ciphers</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Simplified AES</td>
                    <td>Advanced</td>
                    <td>Industry standard symmetric encryption; demonstrates modern security principles in accessible format</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Simplified RSA</td>
                    <td>Advanced</td>
                    <td>Foundational public-key algorithm; demonstrates asymmetric encryption concepts and mathematical foundations</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2><span class="emoji">üìå</span> 4. Testing & Iteration (First Round) (Required) Documented Red-Teaming (First Round)</h2>
        
        <h3>Teams Who Red-Teamed Your Site:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Team 1: Cookies</li>
            <li>Team 2: 101 Team</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Feedback Received:</h3>
        
        <div class="feedback">
            <h4>Team - Cookies</h4>
            <p><strong>Good parts:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Overall everything is great</li>
                <li>Working very well</li>
                <li>Easy to understand</li>
                <li>Easy to use, convenient</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Everything looks great, we would just suggest to add theme option (light/dark or any other colors would be interested)</p>
            <p>Firstly because some people are more used to lighter theme and their eyes are not used to the dark one (especially Diana)</p>
            <p>Secondly because it would suit your website theme</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="feedback">
            <h4>Reviewed by the 101 Team</h4>
            <p><strong><span class="check-icon">‚úÖ</span> What We Liked:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Modern, futuristic look -- the glowing neon header fits the theme well.</li>
                <li>Functional and smooth -- all encryption and decryption tools work without bugs.</li>
                <li>Clear structure -- algorithm selection, input, and output areas are logically placed.</li>
                <li>Consistent UI -- the dark mode with cyan buttons and white text creates a clean, professional vibe.</li>
                <li>Bonus features like file upload and result download are useful additions.</li>
                <li>Excellent logic behind the cipher implementations -- especially Caesar, XOR, Atbash, and Vigen√®re.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p><strong><span class="tool-icon">üîß</span> Suggested Improvement:</strong></p>
            <p>Visual spacing and hierarchy need refinement:</p>
            <p>Currently, all elements are tightly packed together vertically. Increasing padding between sections (especially between input boxes, buttons, and output) would make the interface more breathable and visually organized. This would enhance usability and reduce cognitive load for users.</p>
        </div>
        
        <h3>Changes/Improvements Made:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Changed interface colors to look better together</li>
            <li>Added sky blue buttons and a lighter color palette</li>
            <li>Implemented a light/dark mode toggle so users can choose their preferred theme</li>
            <li>Added more space between sections (input areas, buttons, and results)</li>
            <li>Increased padding around elements to create a more "breathable" layout</li>
            <li>Grouped related items together visually to improve organization</li>
            <li>Made headings larger and more distinct to better show the page structure</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2><span class="emoji">üìå</span> 5. Creative Enhancements (Required)</h2>
        
        <h3>Documented Creative Enhancements</h3>
        
        <h4>Selected Enhancements:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Added blinking/shining stars when users encrypt or decrypt text</li>
            <li>Added neon-style text to make encrypted results look better</li>
            <li>Added user history activities</li>
            <li>Implemented a light/dark mode toggle so users can choose their preferred theme</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4>Issues Encountered:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Star animations didn't work correctly when encryption was running</li>
            <li>The encrypted text didn't change even when users picked different methods</li>
            <li>Some encryption algorithms were not producing unique results</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4>Final Decisions/Solutions:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Tested each encryption algorithm at least 5 times to fix the output problems</li>
            <li>Fixed the code so each encryption method gives different results</li>
            <li>Made sure the visual effects works correctly</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
